## Reptiles & Amphibians (ge') gejo [g\uc0\u603 .\u657 \u593 ]\
\
While _Reptile_ is **gejo**, _Amphibian_ is referred to as \'93Water Retile\'94, **swam de\'92gejo**. It is also allowed to use a proper name here.\'a0 So, _Amphibian_ can be naturalize with the Proper Noun to get, **g\uc0\u363 \'92amfib\u275 \'92an** as that is a class of animal.\
\
## Food (gi'-)\
\
The extensiveness of food and food type necessitates a morphological construction for food similar to Animals.\'a0 Food is rewriting in **Verbum** phonology with the prefix **gi\'92-** added. The \'91 causes the same guttural stop like with animals.\'a0 For example: _Bread_ (**gi\'92bred**), _Soup_ (**gi\'92s\uc0\u363 p**), and _Steak_ (**gi\'92st\u257 k**)\
\
## Elements (g\uc0\u257 -) g\u257 jo [ge\u618 .\u657 \u593 ]\
\
Naturally occurring elements (**g\uc0\u257 jo**) that are a part of the periodic table use the English name spelled using **Verbum** phonology.\'a0 Each element name is preceded by the qualifier morpheme (**g\u257 -**) to identify that the next work is an element. So, when using the word _Gold_, in **Verbum** it would be **g\u257 g\u333 ld** and _Helium_ would be **g\u257 h\u275 l\u275 \'92um**.\
\
## Measurements (g\uc0\u275 -) g\u275 jo [gi:.\u657 \u593 ]\
\
There are a few base measures (**g\uc0\u275 jo**) that have distinct **Verbum** words like _Meter_ (**bran**[br\'e6n) and _Mile_ (**br\u257 n**[bre\u618 n]) but when it comes to more obscure measures like _Volt, Farad, and Newton_ the morpheme qualifier (**g\u275 -**) is added to identify the next word as a measure using **Verbum** phonology of the English measure. So, a _Radian_ becomes **g\u275 r\u257 d\u275 \'92an** and a _Joule_ becomes **g\u275 j\u363 l**.\
\
## Plants & Trees\
\
When referring to _Plants_ and _Trees_ (not fruits or things considered food \'96 see above) use the Proper Name morpheme (**g\uc0\u363 -**) as an Adjective to the word for _Plant_ (**trim**) or _Tree_ (**trom**).\'a0 So, when saying _Birch Tree_, you would say **trom g\u363 ber\u263 ** or a _Rose Plant_, **trim g\u363 r\u333 z**\
